article.headline: Chicago St 67, Centenary 63
article.story: SHREVEPORT, La. (AP) -- Chicago State made good on 10-of-12 free throws in the final minute for a 67-63 win over Centenary Thursday night, snapping a 12-game losing streak. The two teams swapped leads over several possessions in the second half, before David Holston's 3-pointer put Chicago State (2-14, 1-4 Mid-Con) ahead for good. The Cougars' biggest lead would be only eight points and Centenary managed to shrink it back to three on several occasions, but the Gents' best chance to pull closer was disrupted by a turnover with 1:03 left in the game with the score at 57-53. Centenary (2-13, 0-4) began fouling with 55 seconds left in the game. Kourtney Calvin led Chicago State with 21 points. Royce Parran added 15 and Holston had 14. Chris Watson led the Gents 26 and Bryan Baumann added 11.
